# Design System

No Tailwind, Bootstrap, or CSS frameworks. Use existing custom properties and classes.

## Tokens (`:root` in `assets/css/main.css` or embedded `<style>`)

| Token | Role |
|-------|------|
| `--primary`, `--primary-mid`, `--primary-light` | Brand greens |
| `--secondary-cont`, `--secondary-dim` | Gold CTAs |
| `--lime`, `--lime-dim` | Accent highlights |
| `--bg`, `--surface`, `--surface-low` | Backgrounds |
| `--on-surface`, `--outline` | Text and borders |
| `--font-head`, `--font-body`, `--font-label` | Montserrat, Sora, Hanken Grotesk |
| `--r-sm` … `--r-full`, `--shadow-*` | Radius and elevation |

Change colors only via `:root` — do not hardcode hex in new rules unless matching an existing one-off.

## Typography utilities

- `.t-xl`, `.t-lg`, `.t-md` — headings (Montserrat)
- `.t-label` — uppercase labels (Hanken Grotesk)
- `.t-body`, `.t-sm` — body copy (Sora)

## Layout & components

- `.container` — max-width 1280px, horizontal padding
- `.section-gap` / section padding — keep vertical rhythm consistent
- `.section-header` — centered section titles
- `.btn`, `.btn-primary`, `.btn-gold`, `.btn-outline`, `.btn-ghost-white`
- `.glass` — frosted panels with `backdrop-filter`
- `.fade-up` — scroll-reveal target (paired with JS)

## Fonts

Keep Google Fonts link: Montserrat (head), Sora (body), Hanken Grotesk (labels).

## Example — new CTA button

```css
/* ✅ GOOD — uses tokens */
.my-cta {
  background: var(--primary);
  font-family: var(--font-label);
  border-radius: var(--r-full);
}

/* ❌ BAD — arbitrary colors */
.my-cta { background: #033; font-family: Arial; }
```
